    <bioghist encodinganalog="545">
      <head>Biographical History</head>
      <p>George Smyser of Utica, New York was an Abraham Lincoln researcher, collector and scholar.</p>
    </bioghist>
    <scopecontent encodinganalog="520">
      <head>Scope and Contents of the Collection</head>
      <p>The <emph render="bold">George Smyser Papers</emph> consist of <emph render="bold">Correspondence</emph>, 1905-1955, of Smyser and his wife, and a collection of <emph render="bold">Speeches</emph>, 1863-1943, mostly about Abraham Lincoln.</p>
    </scopecontent>
    <arrangement encodinganalog="351$a">
      <head>Arrangement of the Collection</head>
      <p>Both series are arranged chronologically.</p>
    </arrangement>
